{"actual_usd":0.12429,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":186,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24300,"reply":"\"I don't think you can split them apart that neatly.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron, watching the pale morning light catch on the workshop floor.* \"If Easter is only a symbol, then it's a lovely one—but lovely things don't save a man. Christian faith hangs its coat on something that happened in the flesh. An empty tomb. A risen Jesus. Otherwise we're just calling winter by a prettier name.\"\n\n*I glance toward the shelf where that cracked old mug sits, quiet as a witness.* \"Now—symbol, yes. Meaning, certainly. New life, absolutely. But those come because of the thing itself, not instead of it. If Christ didn't truly rise, then faith goes thin fast, and honest folk ought to say so plain.\"\n\n\"What’s pressing under your question—belief, or the kind of truth a thing has to have before you can trust it?\"","rolling_24h_usd":70.51101999999999,"run_id":"3cd60177-55d4-460e-bfcf-0bb1404e0b4d"}
